// TEST: bare_module_import_rejected
// EXPECT: error E4014 at 13:6
//
// Q-import-reject (§12.2 / DQ8): a `use` of a module path with NEITHER a
// brace-list NOR a wildcard — a bare `use core.error` — is not a v1 import
// form. The type checker rejects it with `E4014` and points at the braced form
// (`use core.error.{ ... }`). Module-qualified access (referring to symbols as
// `core.error.Error`) is deferred to v1.x alongside aliasing; the only two v1
// import forms are the braced list and the discouraged wildcard. The braced and
// wildcard forms keep working (see the `stdlib/` no_errors fixtures).
module main

use core.error

fn main() -> Void {
  println("unreachable past the rejected import")
}
